hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Null condition for radial light ($d\phi=0$, $ds^2=0$):
   $$
   -\left(1+\frac{\rho^2}{R^2}\right)c^2dt^2+\frac{d\rho^2}{1+\rho^2/R^2}=0
   \;\Rightarrow\;
   dt=\pm\frac{d\rho}{c(1+\rho^2/R^2)}
   $$
2. Inbound from boundary to center:
   $$
   t_{\rm in}
   =\int_{\infty}^{0}\frac{-d\rho}{c(1+\rho^2/R^2)}
   =\frac{R}{c}\left[\arctan\frac{\rho}{R}\right]_{0}^{\infty}
   =\frac{\pi R}{2c}
   $$
3. Outbound from center to boundary:
   $$
   t_{\rm out}
   =\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{d\rho}{c(1+\rho^2/R^2)}
   =\frac{\pi R}{2c}
   $$
4. Proper waiting time at $\rho=0$ equals global coordinate time: $\Delta t_\text{wait} = \Delta\tau_0$.
5. Total elapsed global time:
   $$
   \Delta t
   =t_{\rm in}+\Delta\tau_0+t_{\rm out}
   =\frac{\pi R}{c}+\Delta\tau_0
   $$
